Etymology. The new species is named after the toponym “Diksam”, an elevated limestone plateau (~ 1000m asl) south of the central Haggeher Mountains, on Socotra Island ( Yemen ), harbouring a significant number of local endemics in both plants and animals (for maps, see
Cheung & DeVantier 2006
).
